Summary
"No Surprises" is a song by the British alternative rock band Radiohead. It was released as the third and final single from the group's 1997 album "OK Computer". Accompanied by a music video that featured a single shot of singer Thom Yorke's head in a plastic bubble that filled with water, the single peaked at number four in the United Kingdom. Radiohead wrote "No Surprises" while touring with the band R.E.M. in 1995. "No Surprises" was the first song Radiohead recorded on the first day of recording sessions for "OK Computer".
